            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", Alfa Romeo, and Lotus, among many others. That leads us into the video above, which features a 1977 Lancia Beta Montecarlo that was created by a man named Gabriel Valentin for Martini Racing. The YouTube clip is in French, so you may have to add closed captioning if you are not familiar with the language.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Gabriel Valentin has been passionate about rallying, specifically the World Rally Championship, since the late 1990s. Although he was just a child at the time, his father was a sponsor at Dakar and had two ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
